  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2005-09-15",
    "date": "2005-11-02T22:22:01Z",
    "text": "American Evacuation Planning Act - Amends the Homeland Security Act to include among the functions of the Federal Emergency Management Agency leading and supporting the Nation in a comprehensive, risk-based emergency management program of preparing communities and individuals, particularly those with special needs, for evacuation from a major disaster by coordinating with state and local governments in preparing or improving community evacuation plans and encouraging individuals to establish a personal plan."
